There are few words... MY NEW FAVORITE PLACE!!!  I see Vincenzos on my news feed...  22nd out of the top 50 Italian restaurants in the UNITED STATES! HERE IN LOUSIVILLE!!!  I quickly made a reservation after taking a look at the menu. From the start, we walk in the doors... place a napkin in my lap! What!!! It felt fancy and cozy all at the same time. John was our server and he was informative, friendly and after much deliberation I let him choose my dinner. Best choice EVER! The food from beginning as in appetizer to end dessert was MIND BLOWING!(sp) they plate the food right in front of you. I am drooling just thinking of which one of the delicious dishes I ate. From the fresh tomato and fresh mozzarella drizzled with pesto and balsamic. Felt like I should be eatting it outside in my garden on a sweet breeze summer day. I'm thinking I could eat every day! I could go on and on. Food prices would be what you would expect. $25-50 for dinner plate.  Worth every penny! Did I mention that one of the chefs came and shook our hands, thanked usfor coming. I wanted to grab him and give him a big hug! I wanted to dance around the restaurant. Our server said he wouldn't stop me. Lol! Handicap friendly. They have valet if your worried about parking. Love. LOVE. LOVEEEE!!!

I decided to surprise my girlfriend on our anniversary by taking her out to something special. And Vincenzo's surely did not disappoint! All of my special requests were more than accommodated. Close off-street parking was easy to find. We entered the restaurant and were amazed by the elegance and hospitality. We were seated immediately and then greeted by Mr. Vincenzo himself. The wait staff were simply excellent. Every dish was exquisite. We had a special seafood pasta appetizer, cesar salad, the veal Madeira, and the ravioli. Every dish was finished and presented tableside, an old-school and refreshing tradition. Then, our waiter Casey surprised us with a decorated dessert plate for our anniversary, compliments of Mr. Vincenzo. Casey helped me to pay the bill without it coming to the table, one of my requests. What a great establishment! Thank you Vincenzo and family for helping me create a magical night for my girlfriend and I! You have earned a loyal patron. We can't wait for our next visit!

Sat at their bar Friday next get for dinner and returned again Saturday for drinks and dessert.  The bartender may not have known what to expect considering we weren't really dressed for the occasion per se.  But we hit it off soon enough and the time spent overall will always be remembered as a key component to our 17th anniversary weekend!  Friday we had the ravioli--it was absolutely to die for!  In a lovely cream sauce with grilled chicken, spinach, mushrooms, and cherry tomatoes.  My husband was able to get his without mushrooms and thoroughly enjoyed his as well.  It was so good, by the time I thought to capture a picture too much was gone to do it justice!  Once we ordered, we got to talking with the bartender (sorry I TOTALLY stink at names--great guy though) and told him we were in town for our 17th.  He immediately gave us some pointers as to where to visit and then after lovely drinks and dinner, he surprised us with a half order of both tiramisu and white chocolate cheesecake with a raspberry drizzle.  It was hands down THE BEST tiramisu I have ever eaten!  We enjoyed his company and the desert so much we were turned on Saturday night for an encore--great place and great ambiance--we will definitely be back!

i wish there was a way to give 0 stars because the experience i had doesnt even deserve 1. we went the friday after valentines day and we were disgusted to our stomachs. we ended up paying $106- for 2 people with NO DRINKS for service and food you would receive at Applebees! TO start the night off my bread roll had a LONG blonde hair hanging out of it-- i have black hair. Then my friends ordered a $14 salad only for the salad to come out wilted and comparable to the side salad at Texas roadhouse. THEN once we FINALLY  received our food- the portions were ridiculous, The meals we ordered did not look like the pictures of the exact meal on the website. We ALL left STILL Hungry!!!! towards the end of my meal the waiter filled up my water glass only for a big black piece of "Gunk" to fall into my glass. when i brought it to the waiters attention, they laughed and said it was just parsley! it most certainly was NOT parsley! I then had enough and asked to speak for to a manger or someone in charge--- after 20 MINUTES of waiting -- NO ONE CAME OUT- so we signed our credit card slip and left!!! i am so disappointed, i wanted a nice evening with my friends and my sweetie for valentines day-- only to feel as though i had a wasted my money on a NOT SPECIAL experience at all!

I was very disappointed with our overall experience here. The atmosphere was very nice and our waitress Sonja was nice but I feel the food is way over priced for what you get. My husband and I ordered a $14.00 Cesar salad to share and when they brought it out there was only a tiny portion of salad on our plates, not to mention the fact that the salad looked and tasted like it came straight out of a salad kit from Walmart. Very disappointed. My friend and her husband were eating with us as well and she found a long blonde hair hanging out of one of her rolls...no one at our table had long blonde hair....When it was brought to the waitresses attention she seemed to be somewhat apologetic but seemed to just kind of brush it off...We then received our entrees after a long time of waiting to the table...The portions were very disappointing considering how much the entrees cost and the taste was NOT anything spectacular.  We tried to visit with each other and enjoy the meals as much as we could. The icing on the cake was when one of the waiters came around to fill my friends water glass and a big black looking glob dropped into her water glass.....she immediately asked what that was and asked to have another glass. The guy said he didn't know what it was but would get her another water glass...Our waitress came by and we told her what had just happened and she made the comment "Oh no, it was probably parsley." "Parsley is everywhere around here." She didn't seem to think it was a huge deal.....We then asked to speak to the a manager and waited for about 20 min or so and no one came out...we eventually just paid and left....We will never be going back here and are very disappointed that we spent $125.00 "for two people" for the kind of food and experience that we had.

We should have known the evening was going to be full of problems from the very beginning. Waiting at the bar to be seated, the bartender sighed with relief & thanked us for not ordering a drink. Sorry sir, the beer you ordered is not cold. Sorry sir, we have sold out of salmon. Normally, part of the ambiance is great service and tableside preparation. Not tonight. My steak was well past the medium ordered and my companions dish was served cold. The remake was even worse with a scallop seared too much on one side and left uncooked on the other. I would have been embarrassed to ask my customer to pay for all of this, but no offer to make any adjustments were made. What has happened to this restaurant?

I have been here a few times in the last couple of years. I like the staff and the food is pretty good. However a couple of things really hurt this place. Number one is the costs. Compared to the other Italian eateries the prices are not justified when you can go to a number of other places, get just as good food (if not better) and spend half the money. Secondly, I was not pleased after my most recent visit to find they are now charging automatic gratuity for everyone (called a "service charge"). I was not informed of this and left a $20 tip besides $15 I was already charged. To be fair, it was circled on the bill and I failed to notice it until well after the fact. Not a fan of this practice and it is no wonder the crowd on a Saturday night was pretty small. I can understand why they offer Groupons all the time after seeing that too. Speaking of which,  I bought one that was a $50 value and my bill was still $44 if that tells you anything. Again while I think there are good people who work here, sadly I don't think I will be back anytime in the near future.
